  "properties": {
    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "This chatbot is designed to help you explore how networking components function and how data flows across the Internet.\r\n\r\n### Do This:\r\n- Work with a partner and interact with the AI chatbot to identify the function of each networking component on your activity guide.\r\n- Use the activity guide  to **label each component** and **draw arrows** to show how data moves\r\n- Once you've finished, upload a photo of your diagram to the chatbot and ask for feedback.\r\n\r\n**Example Questions to Ask the Chatbot**\r\n- What does a router do when I visit a website?\r\n- What is a switch? How does it direct data?\r\n- How does a server help load a webpage?\r\n- What happens when I send a message online?\r\n\r\n**Tip**\r\n- Be specific with your questions, and if answers are too vague, or you don't understand them, rephrase your question for better results!   ",
    "aichat_settings": {
      "initialCustomizations": {
        "selectedModelId": "gpt-4o-mini",
        "temperature": 0.3,
        "systemPrompt": "",
        "retrievalContexts": [
          "Internet Tower: a piece of infrastructure that sends and receives wireless signals\nrouter: a type of computer that forwards data across a network\nserver: a powerful computer that stores and delivers websites, files, and messages when requested by a user\nswitch: a component that helps send data to the right place inside a local network\n"
        ],
        "modelCardInfo": {
          "botName": "Network Chatbot",
          "description": "The Network Chatbot is designed to help students understand how the Internet works by providing clear, concise explanations about networking components, data flow, and Internet communication. It supports student learning by answering questions related to routers, switches, servers, Internet towers, Wi-Fi, Ethernet, and data transmission protocols.",
          "intendedUse": "Classroom learning: Supports lessons on network infrastructure and Internet communication.\nInteractive exploration: Helps students engage with key concepts through question-driven inquiry.\nGuided student activities: Used alongside the Internet Simulator and Activity Guide to reinforce understanding.\nSelf-paced review: Students can revisit concepts by interacting with the chatbot at any time.",
          "limitationsAndWarnings": "Only provides networking-related responses: The chatbot will not answer unrelated topics and will redirect students if they go off-topic.\nDoes not replace teacher instruction: It is a supplementary tool, meant to reinforce learning, not replace classroom discussions.\nResponses are simplified: While explanations are accurate, some technical details may be omitted to maintain clarity.\nCannot diagnose network issues: The chatbot explains general networking concepts, but won't troubleshoot real-world Internet problems.",
          "testingAndEvaluation": "Accuracy Testing: The chatbot’s responses have been evaluated against lesson objectives to ensure correctness and alignment with educational standards.\n",
          "exampleTopics": [
            "Understanding Network Components  \"What does a router do?\" \"How does a switch direct data?\" \"What is the purpose of a server?\" \"How does an Internet tower connect me to the Internet?\"",
            "How Data Moves Across the Internet  \"What happens when I visit a website?\" \"How does my data travel when I send an email?\" \"Why is my Internet connection sometimes slow?\" \"What happens if my data gets lost on the Internet?\"",
            ""
